              <img src="/images/jen2.png" alt="Jen" class="hero-image float-start ms-3" style="max-width: 40%;">
              <h4 style="font-weight: bold; color: #3b7a57; font-family:system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;">Who We Are</h4>
              <p>Our founder, Jen, used to be homeless. One especially cold winter in Utah, 7 of her friends froze to death. Jen, 
                no longer homeless, decided that she wanted to help those suffering from homelessness. She started the 
                Turtle Shelter Project with that intent - to <a href="/how-to-help" style="color: black; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;">help those that suffer from homelessness. </a>
                We strive to use our time and resources to make the lives of our homeless friends easier, and we could use your help!
              </p>
            </div><br><br>
            <div id="item-2">
              <img src="/images/whatwedo.png" alt="Two women wearing vests" class="hero-image float-end ms-3" style="max-width: 35%;">
              <h4 style="font-weight: bold; color: #3b7a57; font-family:system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif">How We Help</h4>
              <p>We manufacture and distribute Turtle Shelter Vests.<br><p><a href="/about-us" style="color: black; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;">What are Turtle Shelter Vests?</a></p>
                 They are a high tech but simple solution to help save countless lives - a portable shelter that you can carry with you, 
                 just as a turtle carries its shell.<br>
              These high tech foam vests are inexpensive while keeping a person warm in down to 10 degrees below zero. They help save lives 
            and alleviate suffering! <br> We have the expertise and the resources to manufacture and hand out these life saving 
            miracle vests! Want to <a href="/how-to-help" style="color: black; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;">help</a>?</p>
            </div><br><br>
            <div id="item-3">
              <h4 style="font-weight: bold; color: #3b7a57; font-family:system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif">How You Can Help Too</h4>
              <p>You can help too! We have created this organization not only to help alleviate the suffering of the homeless, but also
                 to generate the ability to serve for the community! There are many ways that you can help us! <br>
                 <p><a href="/volunteer" style="color: black; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;">Sign up to be a volunteer</a></p>
                 You can volunteer your time to help the homeless! By signing up to be a volunteer, you can tell us the times that you are 
                 available to help from the comfort of your own home. We will get the materials and the knowledge to you so that you can
                 make Turtle Shelter Vests yourself! <br><br>
                 <img src="/images/event.png" alt="Image of Event" class="hero-image float-start ms-3">
                 <p style=><a href="/event" style="color: black; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;">Request to host an event</a></p>
                 You can also help by hosting an event! You can invite you friends, family, members of your church, club, and so 
                 much more! By requesting an event, you can specify the time and date that works for you, and we will verify with you 
                 and then come to you with the expertise and the supplies! Get together with others that have the desire to help and
                 lift your community! <br><br><br>
                 <br><br><p><a href="https://turtleshelterproject.org/checkout/donate?donatePageId=5b6a44c588251b72932df5a0" style="color: black; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;">Donate!</a></p>
                 Have the desire to help out, but not the time to help with a vest? You can also send a donation to the organization to help us 
                 as we work to make the vests. We can't do any work here on the ground without funding, so a donation helps more than you know! 
                 Everything that you can do is appreciated!
              </p>
